Dataset

General statistics of the training corpus (train_split.csv)
Title + Description

Text length in words
Average length: 37.85 words
90th percentile (p90): 48 words
99th percentile (p99): 70 words

Vocabulary statistics
Unique words: 47284
Rare words (frequency = 1): 33.59%

Tokenizer conclusions
19k → sequences become longer
21k → higher UNK‑rate, sequence length barely decreases
Optimal vocab_size = 20000

Choosing max sequence length
p99 after SentencePiece = 109 tokens
max_len = 256 fully covers the corpus
Tokenization algorithm Byte Pair Encoding

Dataset class
Receives a dataframe, the SentencePiece tokenizer, and max_len
Concatenates Title and Description into a single text
Tokenizes the text using SPMTokenizer with fixed‑length output
Converts class labels to zero‑based indexing
Returns a dictionary with input_ids tensor and labels tensor

Overall model architecture:
- token and positional embeddings
- a stack of N identical encoder blocks
- normalization
- classifier

The attention block is implemented manually:
- linear projections of the input into Q, K, V matrices of size d_model
- splitting into num_heads heads: shape changes from (batch, seq_len, d_model) to (batch, heads, seq_len, head_dim)
- computing the attention score matrix
- applying the attention mask so the model ignores PAD tokens
- softmax along the last dimension
- weighted sum of Value vectors
- concatenation of heads and a final linear projection

Feed‑Forward Network
- the first layer expands the dimensionality: d_model → hidden_dim
- ReLU
- the second layer reduces the dimensionality back: hidden_dim → d_model
FFN strengthens local features of each token

Encoder Block
Uses a pre‑norm scheme, which ensures stable training
- LayerNorm before attention
- Multi‑Head Self‑Attention
- Residual connection
- LayerNorm before FFN
- Feed‑Forward Network
- Residual connection
- Attention Mask

To ensure correct attention behavior, a binary mask is created:
1 — real token
0 — PAD
The mask is expanded to the shape (batch, 1, 1, seq_len) and passed into every attention block
This prevents padding tokens from influencing attention computation